Usage: python scrub_user.py [USER_UID] [NUMBER_OF_BUCKETS_TO_BE_PARALLELLY_PROCESSED -- optional]

Input parameters:
USER_UID                                     - UID of the user that has to be scrubbed.
NUMBER_OF_BUCKETS_TO_BE_PARALLELLY_PROCESSED - Number of buckets that can be parallely scrubbed.
                                               Default value: 4

Examples:
  python scrub_user.py rolland.s --> scrubs all buckets of user 'rolland.s'

